ğŸ“– Description

This project implements an Arduino-based vehicle ignition system using face detection to prevent unauthorized access and vehicle theft. The system uses OpenCV with Haarcascade and LBPH algorithms for real-time face recognition, ensuring only authorized users can start the vehicle. In case of an intruder, the system sends a Telegram alert with the captured photo to the owner, along with an option for remote access approval. It also integrates an accident detection module for enhanced safety, making it a secure and cost-effective solution for modern vehicle security.

